    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The reason for this behaviour is that references to internal functions in the constructor always create an identifier for the creation-time and the run-time aspect of the function, because the function pointer might be stored in storage.\r\n\r\nCurrently, I cannot think of a nice way to resolve this issue. The simplest case of just directly calling the function can get rid of the runtime identifier, but it would be rather hacky.",
